<doc id="246049" wikidata="Q5297836" url="?curid=246049" title="Dorimène Roy Desjardins">
<text>Marie-Clara Dorimène Roy Desjardins (September 17, 1858 – June 14, 1932) and her husband Alphonse Desjardins were co-founders of the &quot;Caisses populaires Desjardins&quot; (today Desjardins Group), a forerunner of North American credit unions. She was appointed honorary member of the Union régionale des caisses populaires Desjardins de Québec in 1923.

